         <p outputclass="box" class="- topic/p ">This SAS is effective for audits of financial statements for periods
                ending on or after December 15, 2023. A link to the final SAS and other resources
                can be found on the page “<xref scope="external" format="html" class="- topic/xref " href="https://www.aicpa.org/interestareas/frc/auditattest/auditing-standards-information-and-resources.html">Recently Issued Auditing and Attestation Standards: Information and
                    Resources</xref>,” which is available using the audit and attest link in the
                financial reporting center at aicpa.org.</p>
      </note>
      <p outputclass="ps_para_number" id="UUID-1911b3ac-218a-078f-9079-2004d1718a11_aag-afi8.01" class="- topic/p ">
         <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">8.01</b> This case study uses the
            following three scenarios to illustrate how an entity’s use of a service organization
            affects the auditor’s considerations in planning and performing auditing procedures
            related to assertions about financial instrument transactions:</p>
      <ol outputclass="a" class="- topic/ol ">
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">
               <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">
                  <xref format="dita" class="- topic/xref " href="../../aag-afi/aag-afi8/aag-afi8_scenario_a/aag-afi8_scenario_a.dita#UUID-1911b3ac-218a-078f-9079-2004d1718a11_UUID-4a8ef84d-e2e7-0a74-31f2-8209e78e09f5">Scenario A — Directed Investing Arrangement With One Service
                            Organization: a Broker-Dealer</xref>
               </i>. In this scenario, a
                    user entity initiates trades, and a broker-dealer executes the trades and holds
                    and services financial instruments purchased. <ph class="- topic/ph ">
                  <fn callout="2" id="UUID-1911b3ac-218a-078f-9079-2004d1718a11-aag-afi8-fn2" class="- topic/fn ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Maintaining custody of securities, either in physical or electronic
                            form, is referred to as holding, and performing ancillary services is
                            referred to as servicing. Examples of servicing transactions are
                            collecting dividends and interest and distributing that income to the
                            entity and receiving notification of corporate actions, such as stock
                            splits.</p>
                  </fn>
                  <xref type="fn" class="- topic/xref " href="aag-afi8.dita#UUID-1911b3ac-218a-078f-9079-2004d1718a11/UUID-1911b3ac-218a-078f-9079-2004d1718a11-aag-afi8-fn2"/>
               </ph>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">
               <xref format="dita" class="- topic/xref " href="../../aag-afi/aag-afi8/aag-afi8_scenario_b/aag-afi8_scenario_b.dita#UUID-1911b3ac-218a-078f-9079-2004d1718a11_UUID-4785567a-486c-ef14-0648-eddb1fe1aec3">
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Scenario B — Discretionary Investing
                            Arrangement With Two Service Organizations: an Investment Adviser and a
                            Broker-Dealer</i>
               </xref>. In this scenario, the user entity has
                    authorized an investment adviser to initiate trades on its behalf, and a
                    broker-dealer executes the trades and holds and services the financial
                    instruments purchased.</p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">
               <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">
                  <xref format="dita" class="- topic/xref " href="../../aag-afi/aag-afi8/aag-afi8_scenario_c/aag-afi8_scenario_c.dita#UUID-1911b3ac-218a-078f-9079-2004d1718a11_UUID-0957a1a9-1378-b9fe-15b1-d63b27fd3514">Scenario C — Discretionary Investing Arrangement With One Service
                            Organization: a Broker-Dealer</xref>
               </i>. In this scenario, a
                    user entity has authorized a broker-dealer to initiate trades on its behalf and
                    also to execute the trades and hold and service the financial instruments
                    purchased.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
      <p outputclass="ps_para_number" id="UUID-1911b3ac-218a-078f-9079-2004d1718a11_aag-afi8.02" class="- topic/p ">
         <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">8.02</b> <xref format="dita" class="- topic/xref " href="../../aag-afi/aag-afi8/aag-afi_information_that_applies_to/aag-afi8_description_of_the_entity/aag-afi8_description_of_the_entity.dita#UUID-1911b3ac-218a-078f-9079-2004d1718a11_UUID-94a919f0-c681-0681-bfaf-68eebc063812/UUID-1911b3ac-218a-078f-9079-2004d1718a11_aag-afi8.03">Paragraphs 8.03–.09</xref> present information that is applicable to all the
            scenarios, including</p>
      <ul outputclass="ul bullet" class="- topic/ul ">
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">a description of the user entity.</p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">a summary of the accounting considerations.</p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">types of potential misstatements of the user entity’s assertions about its
                    financial instruments and financial instrument transactions.</p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">inherent risk factors the auditor considers in planning the audit.</p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">the timing of substantive procedures.</p>
         </li>
      </ul>
